GlooKit.GlooFramework

Class ColSpan

  • java.lang.Object
    • GlooKit.GlooFramework.KitBit
      • GlooKit.GlooFramework.Div
        • GlooKit.GlooFramework.ColSpan

  • public class ColSpan
extends Div
    A ColSpan is a Div which has a list of children that will be drawn vertically from top to bottom in the order added.
    Since:
    1.0
    See Also:
    Div

    • Constructor Detail

      • ColSpan

        public ColSpan(KitBit... children)
        Overloads the default ColSpan constructor to only take a list of children. Defaults to being right and bottom justified, having no spacing, and taking up all the width and height it can.
        Parameters:
        children - possibly many KitBits, which are children of this ColSpan. Can take any number of KitBits

      • ColSpan

        public ColSpan(int X,
               java.lang.String W,
               KitBit... children)
        Overloads the default ColSpan constructor to only take a horizontal justification, a formatting String for setting the width, and a list of children. Defaults to being bottom justified, having no vertical spacing, and taking up all the height it can.
        Parameters:
        X - int of the horizontal justification, as defined in the KitBit class
        W - a valid formatting String for setting the width, as defined in the KitBit class
        children - possibly many KitBits, which are children of this ColSpan. Can take any number of KitBits

      • ColSpan

        public ColSpan(int X,
               int Y,
               java.lang.String W,
               java.lang.String H,
               KitBit... children)
        Constructs a ColSpan with the normal parameters of the default KitBit constructor.
        Parameters:
        X - int of the horizontal justification, as defined in the KitBit class
        Y - int of the vertical justification, as defined in the KitBit class
        W - a valid formatting String for setting the width, as defined in the KitBit class
        H - a valid formatting String for setting the height, as defined in the KitBit class
        children - possibly many KitBits, which are children of this ColSpan. Can take any number of KitBits

    • Method Detail

      • drawFrame

        public void drawFrame(float X,
                      float Y,
                      float W,
                      float H,
                      float Z)
        Overrides the drawFrame(float, float, float, float, float) method of Div to properly calculate the position of all of the children of this ColSpan before calling drawFrame on each of the children.
        Overrides:
        drawFrame in class Div
        Parameters:
        X - float for the horizontal position of the bottom left corner of this KitBit on the screen, measured in pixels from the left side of the screen
        Y - float for the vertical position of the bottom left corner of this KitBit on the screen, measured in pixels from the bottom of the screen
        W - float for the width of this KitBit on the screen, measured in pixels
        H - float for the height of this KitBit on the screen, measured in pixels
        Z - float for the z-coordinate of this KitBit on the screen, ranging from -1 to +1, where +1 is closest to the screen and -1 is furthest from the screen. This does not change the width or height of this KitBit but determines whether this KitBit is drawn in front of or behind another KitBit.
